<br>
Started by calling in two enchanters with fixed duration invis spells and let them mez and hold those two guards, then I call in a cleric or two, a warrior, and ranger.  Let them kill those guards and get the room secure.  Call in a bard for mana and continue to CoH the rest of the raid.<br>
<br>
Disclaimer: It has been at least 2 months since I've called a raid there so things may have been changed.  Always be sure to scout an area first if possible. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227684" target="Magelo"><span style="filter:glow(color=blue,strength=2);width=100%;"><i><b><span style="font-size:large;">Trallos Drachen</span></b></i></span></a><br><b>Conjurer of Firiona Vie</b><br><b>High Marshall of the <a href="http://pub40.ezboard.com/bringofthelight" target="RoTL">Ring of the Light</a></b></center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=trallosdrachen>Trallos Drachen</A> at: 3/5/03 11:43:19 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ptarmiganca>PtarmiganCA</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#333333>(3/7/03 11:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1772.topic&index=22>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: CotH in Chardok</span><hr size=1> Also make sure that one of the initial toons can snare, especially if you have to start fighting before a sufficient force has been cothed in.<br>
<br>
Sarnaks will run and they are very social, and the incoming train will wipe most raids that still hunt for xp in Chardok.<br>
